Zimbabwe Police Arrest Daily News Editor, Reporter

-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a
-- 
2011-12-02T16:26:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/zimbabwe-police-arrest-daily-news-editor-reporter-1-.html
Zimbabwean police arrested Stanley
Guma, the editor of the privately owned Daily News newspaper,
and Xolisani Ncube, a reporter from the same publication, the
Voluntary Media Council of  Zimbabwe  said in an e-mailed
statement today.  The two were arrested on criminal defamation charges,
Guthrie Munyukwi, the assistant editor, said in an interview
from Harare today. Wayne Bvudzijena, a police spokesman, was not
immediately available for comment.  Police later in the day released Guma and Ncube, according
to Guthrie Munyukwi, an assistant editor at the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Godfrey Marawanyika in Johannesburg at 
 gmarawanyika@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
